{
  "texts": [
    "This implication is crucial since it will be difficult for the developers to design the system without knowing how explainable the interface should be.",
    "Bunt et al. (2012) discussed the dilemma of on-demand explanations about \"why\" users require explanations (Bunt et al., 2012).",
    "Additionally, our research contributes to the trust and transparency implications of user-centric explainable systems (Hamm et al., 2023).",
    "Our findings reveal that users mainly desire explanations when encountering unfamiliar content suggestions.",
    "Therefore, as a design recommendation, the developer should allow users to select whether the recommendation is familiar or unfamiliar."
  ]
}